        <header class="project-detail-header">
          <h1 class="project-detail-title">Scripting Language</h1>
          <a href="https://github.com/eightharsh/scripting-language" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="github-link" aria-label="GitHub Repository">
            <svg class="icon github-icon" aria-hidden="true" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.484 2 12.017c0 4.425 2.865 8.18 6.839 9.504.5.092.682-.217.682-.483 0-.237-.008-.868-.013-1.703-2.782.605-3.369-1.343-3.369-1.343-.454-1.158-1.11-1.466-1.11-1.466-.908-.62.069-.608.069-.608 1.003.07 1.531 1.032 1.531 1.032.892 1.53 2.341 1.088 2.91.832.092-.647.35-1.088.636-1.338-2.22-.253-4.555-1.113-4.555-4.951 0-1.093.39-1.988 1.029-2.688-.103-.253-.446-1.272.098-2.65 0 0 .84-.27 2.75 1.026A9.564 9.564 0 0112 6.844c.85.004 1.705.115 2.504.337 1.909-1.296 2.747-1.027 2.747-1.027.546 1.379.202 2.398.1 2.651.64.7 1.028 1.595 1.028 2.688 0 3.848-2.339 4.695-4.566 4.943.359.309.678.92.678 1.855 0 1.338-.012 2.419-.012 2.747 0 .268.18.58.688.482A10.019 10.019 0 0022 12.017C22 6.484 17.522 2 12 2z"/></svg>
          </a>
        </header>
        <section class="project-section" id="introduction">
          <h2>Introduction</h2>
          <p>The Scripting Language project is a lightweight, custom-built language designed for automation tasks. It aims to simplify repetitive workflows by providing a minimalistic syntax and a powerful interpreter, making it easy for developers to write scripts for various use cases.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="project-section" id="technical-details">
          <h2>Technical Details</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Language</strong>: Python</li>
            <li><strong>Core Components</strong>: Custom lexer, parser, and interpreter</li>
            <li><strong>Features</strong>: Variable assignment, basic arithmetic, conditionals, loops</li>
            <li><strong>Performance</strong>: Optimized for small to medium-sized scripts</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        <section class="project-section" id="challenges-faced">
          <h2>Challenges Faced</h2>
          <p>One of the main challenges was designing an efficient parser that could handle nested expressions without significant performance overhead. I also faced issues with error handling, ensuring meaningful error messages for users when their scripts failed to execute.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="project-section" id="future-plans">
          <h2>Future Plans</h2>
          <p>I plan to extend the language by adding support for functions, file I/O operations, and integration with external APIs. Additionally, I aim to improve the interpreter's performance for larger scripts.</p>
        </section>
